<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Components: &lt;segment field name (ST)&gt; ^ &lt;value1 (ST) &amp; value2 (ST) &amp; value3 (ST&#8230;&#8203;&gt;</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Components may be any fields in the PID or PD1. If subcomponents of fields need to be specified, each subcomponent should be listed separately.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Example: &#8230;&#8203;|@PID.5.1EVERYMAN@PID.5.2ADAM@PID.8^M|&#8230;&#8203;</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">SearchConfidenceThreshold</p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">NM</p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Indicates the minimum match confidence for candidates to be returned for the query. The value instructs the queried system to return no records (PID segments) for persons whose "match weight" on the lookup was lower than the user-defined value.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"></td>
